{"body": "How do you mean the folders where `rake notes` should search are application specific? \r\n\r\nAs far as I can see, the only thing application specific is where the developer places the annotations. If `rake notes` just searches all the folders that could contain developer-written code, which would be folders except for `vendor`, `log` and `tmp`, wouldn't everyone be happy?", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4168092", "created_at": "2012-02-25T00:33:26Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/4540#issuecomment-4168092", "updated_at": "2012-02-25T00:33:26Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 4540, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DouweM/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DouweM/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DouweM/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/DouweM", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DouweM/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/DouweM", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DouweM/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/aaaaafa9b7b51e38f4a363605ea6d170?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fbc3bcf55890087daa466e5b73c139af6.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DouweM/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DouweM/received_events", "gravatar_id": "aaaaafa9b7b51e38f4a363605ea6d170", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DouweM/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "DouweM", "type": "User", "id": 159434, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/DouweM/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52382482bd3543c15100ec39"}, "id": 4168092, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/4540"}
